Date: 7/10/1933
Source: Press, The
Author:
Vol / Page: 15
Edition:
Quote: <i>Cracker:</i> Short piece of twisted flax (or silk) at the end of a stock or bullock whip. To make it sting more, some bullockies used to twist in a piece of very fine wire. (C.)
Notes: (Acland Gloss.)

